parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belts to retract properly can lead to accidents or injuries, as the belts may not provide adequate restraint in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The seat belts do not retract after being pulled out

leaving excessive slack in the belt; the seat belts do not tighten up against the driver or passenger; the seat belts do not retract automatically and leave a loose gap when engaged; the seat belts require manual effort to retract; the seat belts do not function properly in humid or cold weather.
